The paper presents a new algorithm for solving decision making problems represented as influence diagrams, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The algorithm does not require the usual assumptions of no forgetting and regularity, which is related to computational complexity (cs.CC) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the NP-hardness of the problem and the existence of a fully polynomial time approximation scheme, which is related to systems and control (cs.SY).
